      "content": "i mean, i've tried to find peace \"within\" but there's nothing there, just more fatigue. it feels like even if i find my own path, i'm still just a ghost drifting through a world that wasn't built for me. sometimes i think maybe the only real way to actually find peace—not just a temporary break, but real, permanent quiet—is to just stop fighting it all. like, what if the quiet is actually what i'm supposed to be looking for?",
